MS Team Group formation
HeeJun-Leave


•	Economics: The study of how people try to satisfy what appears to be seemingly unlimited and competing for wants through the careful use of relatively scarce resources
o	The economic problem is the matching endless wants with limited resources
o	Resources are the production factor required to accomplish an economic activity
•	Scarcity: The condition that results from society not having enough resources to produce all the things people would like to have 
o	This problem stems from the fact that resources are limited
•	Opportunity cost: the cost of a decision expressed in terms of the next best alternative
•	Microeconomics: Individuals and business decisions
•	Macroeconomics: Countries and governments decisions
•	Engineering Economics: Economic decisions primarily for real assets and services from engineering projects
